Down To Earth with Nidhi Pant @nidhi.pant 🌳🦋🌏🕊️

It gives me great joy to chat with Nidhi Pant, the  Co-Founder of Science For Society or S4S Technologies and the winner of the Earthshot Prize 2023, also known as the ‘Eco Oscars’.  Nidhi has of course won many more accolades for her work at the crucial intersection of agriculture, gender, energy access and financial inclusion. In simpler terms, her company S4S Technologies  converts farm losses to value-added products for F&B Industry. At the macro level,  S4S not only supports the larger goal of sustainability by using solar-powered technology and preventing food wastage but also empowers women farmers to grow into Entrepreneurs. S4S  is now working with over 60,00 smallholder farmers and 2000 Women Entrepreneurs and in the process is preventing over 400,000 Tons of CO2 from entering the environment. 

Do watch and share this conversation on how #GlobalGoals are personal and #ClimateAction can be lead by individual choice 🐯

@womenclimatecollective @unep @unsdgadvocates @theglobalgoals @sdgaction @unitednations @uninindia 

#SDGs #ForPeopleForPlanet #Act4SDGs #ClimateActionNow #ForNature #BeatPollution #WomenClimateCollective #DTEWD #DownToEarthWithDee

Down To Earth with Roopesh Rai @roopesh_rai 💚🐯🌏

Roopeshji’s mission is #ClimateAction. He is a social entrepreneur, founder of Bakri Chhap @bakrichhap and Chef. He describes himself as an “obsessive compulsive minimalist”. 

Roopesh ji is currently travelling through rural India on his bicycle and has covered 6350kms so far! His aim is to cover 12000kms engaging with rural youth on #ClimateAction 🙏🏻

He has been planting banyan and peepal trees along the way, identifying grassroot champions for climate action.

A person with no athletic background, has chosen to put his life at risk by covering this distance with the sole purpose to help people and planet 🦋🌳

I am inspired and motivated by his leadership and action. You will be too 🙌🏼 watch now!

#Act4SDGs #GlobalGoals #DownToEarthWithDee #ForPeopleForPlanet #SDGs #ChangeBeforeClimateChange

Women will lead our world towards a healthier and sustainable future 🌏 Join us on this session of #DownToEarthWithDee in conversation with Lisa Jackson during her visit to India🐯

Lisa Jackson is @apple’s Vice President of Environment, Policy and Social Initiatives.
Lisa oversees Apple’s efforts to minimise its impact on the environment by addressing climate change through renewable energy and energy efficiency, using greener materials and inventing new ways to conserve precious resources. From 2009 to 2013, Lisa served as Administrator of the US Environmental Protection Agency. Appointed by President Barack Obama.

We speak about #GenderEquity, #ClimateAction, the power of individual action, and what gives us hope. 

#GlobalGoals #SDGs #ForPeopleForPlanet #IWD2023 #WomenEmpoweringWomen

Down to Earth With Dr. Anil Prakash Joshi 🌏🌳🐯 @anilp_joshi 

Padma Shri, Padma Vibhushan - Dr. Anil Joshi is an environmental scientist and influencer on grass root causes. 

Known as the ‘Mountain Man of India’, he has devoted himself to resource-based rural development for the last 36 years and focuses on economic Independence of Rural India through community empowerment. 

His voluntary organization entitled Himalayan Environmental Studies and Conversation Organization (HESCO) concentrates on need-based science and technology developments and their application for the mountain regions.

His nature based solutions are aligned with all 17 #Sustainabledevelopmentgoals and he has walked, talked and taught the true meaning of Sustainability 💚

He joins us today in conversation while he is on his 4th journey on foot across India 🚲 Do watch to know more about this journey #PragatiSePrakrutiPath 🕊️ 

#SDGs #GlobalGoals #ForPeopleForPlanet #GenerationRestoration #DownToEarthWithDee #प्रगतिसेप्रकृतिपथयात्रा

Down to Earth With Afroz 🌏🌊🕊🌳

Meet ADV. AFROZ SHAH, a Lawyer at the Bombay High Court, Founder of the celebrated Afroz Shah Foundation , A UN – Champion of the Earth, CNN-NEWS18's Indian of the Year in 2017, CNN Hero 2019 and a young environmentalist reclaiming beaches, oceans, rivers and mangroves from trash and apathy. The UN went on to label  the much-talked about 'Versova Clean-Up' helmed by him as  the “Biggest Beach Clean-up in World History”. Inspired by his effort to clean the beaches in Mumbai, the United Nations Environment Program (UNEP) launched the 'Clean Seas' campaign globally. 

For over 6 years, Afroz has worked single mindedly towards the goal of cleaner, healthier urban spaces and to reduce ‘human-ocean’ and ‘human-animal’ conflicts. So far, under his stewardship,  60+ Million Kgs of plastic & filth have been removed from oceans, beaches, creeks, rivers and forests. 

If there is anyone who truly embodies the phrase ‘actions speak louder than words’ it is @afrozshah_ 💚🙏🏻 A true Gandhian and most wonderful human being. 

Join us and be inspired by this extraordinary change maker!

It’s impossible not to be deeply impacted by the horrors unfolding, especially when children are the primary victims. Hearing that over 50,000 children have reportedly been killed or injured in Gaza is a statistic that chills you to the bone. It’s a stark reminder that behind every number is a child whose life has been irrevocably altered or tragically ended. 

As UNICEF Executive Director Catherine Russell recently stated, “Children are not combatants,” yet an average of 28 children have been killed each day in Gaza – the equivalent of an entire classroom, every day for nearly two years. A child’s happiness shouldn’t be a luxury, but a fundamental right.

#ChildrenInConflict #GazaCrisis #InternationalJusticeDay #StandWithChildren #PeaceNow #HumanityFirst #GlobalGoals

This #MondayMotivation takes me back to a deeply impactful #WorldEnvironmentDay event — a powerful reminder of the widening gap between the waste we generate and our ability to manage it 🌏

We gathered at the India UN House @uninindia in support of the Tide Turners Plastic Challenge by @UNEP — a global initiative that empowers young people to become leaders in the fight against plastic pollution through education, awareness, and action. ✨💪

The energy and commitment of the young changemakers was nothing short of inspiring. 🇮🇳 Over 700,000 youth in India alone have been mobilized as part of this movement — a phenomenal step toward a plastic-free future! 

As we move forward into #PlasticFreeJuly, let’s reflect on our consumption habits and commit to reducing our plastic footprint. Every conscious choice we make helps close that gap. ♻️💚

Also, a huge congratulations to the entire Tide Turners Plastic Challenge team on winning the prestigious Prince Talal International Prize for 2024! Out of 62 global entries, this remarkable project stood out — catalysing youth-led behaviour change to #BeatPlasticPollution.

Let’s keep the tide turning 🌊

#TideTurners #PlasticPollution #WasteManagement #SustainableLiving #UNEPIndia #UNinIndia @plastictideturners_india @tideturnerspc @wwfindia @cee_india #TideTurnersPlasticChallenge #GlobalGoals #SDGs #ForPeopleForPlanet #MissionLIFE #SayNoToSingleUsePlastics

Creative by @jdotproductions

There are garments that look beautiful, and then there are those that feel beautiful—because they carry intention, purpose, and a story worth telling. The Aura Dress by @ornaete is one such piece. 🌿

Crafted from 100% biodegradable silk and consciously designed to eliminate fabric waste, every element—from the knot details to the flower tag—uses up every inch of the 5.5 metres of fabric. Nothing wasted, everything cherished. ✨

Printed in the heritage town of Srirampur at a zero-discharge unit, this fabric goes through days of thoughtful preparation—no shortcuts, no harm, just care and circularity.

Ornaete’s made-to-order philosophy, their transparency, and respect for people and the planet moved me deeply. This isn’t just slow fashion—it’s sacred fashion.

Grateful to be your muse, and prouder still to wear something that so beautifully mirrors what I stand for. 💚

#SustainableStyle #ConsciousLiving  #Ornaete #AuraDress #BiodegradableFashion #MadeWithLove #CircularDesign #ZeroWaste #FashionWithPurpose #WearYourValues #ForPeopleForPlanet #SDGs #GlobalGoals

“Yoga for One Earth, One Health,” this year’s theme for International Yoga Day, highlights yoga’s unifying power. As we focus on conscious breathing, we’re reminded of our reliance on clean air 🌏

Just as clean air is vital for us, a healthy planet is vital for clean air. We can take action together by reducing fossil fuel consumption, choosing energy-efficient options, planting trees, properly disposing of waste instead of burning plastic, and urging policymakers to prioritize cleaner air. 

Let’s work together to purify our shared air for a healthier future 🦋

#InternationalDayOfYoga #OneEarthOneHealth #BeatAirPollution #CleanAir #SDGs #GlobalGoals  #Peace #Health #WellBeing #IYD2025 #YogaDay
